President Donald J. Trump was briefed by Dr. Neil Jacobs, head of the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), and Pete T. Gaynor, Acting Administrator of the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA), on the proactive preparations being taken for the 2019 hurricane season. The Trump Administration has conducted extensive outreach to government leaders, the private sector, communities, and families to ensure effective preparedness. Dr. Jacobs provided an update on the projected weather activity for the season, while Acting Administrator Gaynor highlighted FEMA's preparations and ongoing recovery efforts. The President expressed concern for states and territories still recovering from previous hurricanes and last year's wildfires and directed FEMA to ensure adequate preparations and assistance if disaster strikes again.